bug.short_desc: Container's maxWidth is not enforced under some circumstances

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 966 Bug in Showcase / Theme Demo
See attached screenshot.
Tested with Safari 5.0.4 (Mac)
Open the following link:
http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/showcase/#theme
Move the black calculator to the right edge of the container -> the whole inline app is resized and destroys the page layout.

This seems to be a more general issue. For instance, a similar behavior can be found in the window tab of the widget browser (move window to the far right). The bottom line is that the maxWidth of a container is not forced under some very special circumstances.
After some pretty extensive debugging together with Chris, we suspect that the issue is related to a combination of root level grid layout and maxWidth settings in flex columns. However, we could not entirely reproduce the problem.
Here are two playground examples that show some oddities we have discovered so far:
http://tinyurl.com/69mce83 (root == grid) http://tinyurl.com/6zenwkp (maxWidth und flex)

Finally, a complete example
http://tinyurl.com/5vefulm
The sub-container (canvas layout) belongs to a container (grid layout) and has a max-width set. The sub-container has a child widget (first column) with a min-width set to a value higher than the parent's max-width.
Expected: The parent's max-width should win over the child's min-width
Result: If the sub-container has a canvas or grow layout, the child's min-width wins, i.e. overrides the container's max-width.

The final fix took place in the widget code which is responsible for calculation the size hint with its _computeSizeHint method. It checked if the widget itself does not have a min width but the content had one. In that case, the contents had one, it applied it directly without checking any violations with its own max width.
